      • afterRegionCreate

        public void afterRegionCreate(RegionEvent<String,RegionConfiguration> event)
        Description copied from interface: CacheListener
        Handles the event of a region being created. Events are invoked for each individual region that is created.

        Note that this method is only called for creates done in the local vm. To be notified of creates done in remote vms use RegionMembershipListener.afterRemoteRegionCreate(org.apache.geode.cache.RegionEvent<K, V>).
